Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: Effective July 1, 2009, the Organization adopted FASB ASC 740, "Uncertainty in Income Taxes" ('ASC 740'). In accordance with ASC 740, the Organization recognizes the impact of tax positions in the financial statements if that position is more likely than not to be sustained on audit, based on the technical merits of the position. To date, the Organization has not recorded any uncertain tax positions. The Organization recognizes potential accrued interest and penalties related to uncertain tax positions in income tax expense. During the year ended June 30, 2010, the Organization did not recognize any amount in potential interest and penalties associated with uncertain tax positions.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE TAX RETURN WAS RECEIVED FROM THE INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM AND REVIEWED. IT WAS PRESENTED TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE (GOVERNING BOARD) FOR A SECOND REVIEW AND APPROVAL.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: EACH YEAR AT OUR ANNUAL MEETING THE PRESIDENT REQUESTS ALL BOARD MEMBERS TO SIGN-OFF ON THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY FORMS. SEVERAL DAYS PRIOR TO THE MEETING THE PRESIDENT SENDS OUT THIS REQUEST TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS. HE ALSO PROVIDES SIGN-OFF FORMS AT THE MEETING TO ASSURE THAT ALL BOARD MEMBERS, WHO HAVEN'T DONE SO, HAVE SIGNED THE FORMS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE MAKES THE DECISION ON CEO COMPENSATION. THE COMMITTEE INCLUDES THE PAST CHAIRMAN, CURRENT CHAIRMAN AND THE INCOMING CHAIRMAN.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: OUR FINANCIAL STATEMENTS SUMMARIES ARE IN OUR YEARLY ANNUAL REPORT. THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND ALL GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST
SINCE THE FILING OF PRIOR YEAR 2008 TAX RETURN, THERE HAVE BEEN NO CHANGES TO THE AUDIT OVERSIGHT AND SELECTION PROCESS.
